{"author":"Claude","data":{"alias":"obsequious-nonspheric-killdeer","description":"## Why\nThe core deliverable: an `in_progress` ticket should carry the session that started it,\nend-to-end (written on the event AND visible in compiled state). Recording without folding\nproduces no observable outcome, so both halves ship together as one increment.\n\n## What\n- In `claim_core` and `transition_core`, compute `session = resolve_session_id()` (S1); when\n  non-None, add `data[\"session\"]` to the `STATUS(open->in_progress)` event it already\n  writes. Absent -> omit the key entirely -> byte-identical to today.\n- In the reducer's `process_status`, on a fold to `in_progress`, set\n  `state[\"claimed_session\"] = data[\"session\"]` when present. `process_status` already\n  ignores unknown data keys, so old clones tolerate the new key (forward-compatible).\n- Stamp on ANY `open->in_progress` STATUS (claim command AND bare `transition`, incl. the\n  parent-first cascade), not just `claim` — captures the start-of-work session by any path.\n\n## Scope\n- IN: the write (txn) + the reducer fold + tests proving the field lands in state and is\n  absent when the env var is unset.\n- OUT: snapshot/compaction guarantees (S3 read/compaction hardening), pretty read surface\n  (S3), hooks (S4).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Claiming with a session env var set records `claimed_session` in compiled state.\n- [ ] Claiming with no session env var set records nothing (state unchanged; event bytes\n      identical to pre-feature for the no-session path).\n- [ ] A bare `transition <id> open in_progress` records it too (cascade parents included).\n- [ ] `data[\"session\"]` is ignored by a reducer build without the fold (forward-compat test).\n- [ ] Unit/integration tests for present + absent paths.\n\n## Depends on\n- S1 (shared resolver).\n","id":"68ef-da4f-b64b-4903","parent_id":"38ec-5f12-fdf5-4340","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Record the claiming session id on open->in_progress (claim + bare transition)"},"env_id":"724d9d0c-bc4c-4cc4-b96b-1a19356102e2","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783481175971883371,"uuid":"00b18be3-679a-4b2b-b37e-5884ada84c7a"}